  "description": "A normal subgroup is a subgroup NN of a group GG that is \u0026ldquo;symmetric\u0026rdquo; with respect to the rest of the group — it looks the same from every vantage point within GG. Formally, NN is normal (written N⊴GN \\trianglelefteq G) if gNg−1=NgNg^{-1} = N for every g∈Gg \\in G. This condition says that conjugating NN by any element of GG — moving to a different \u0026ldquo;perspective\u0026rdquo; within the group — gives NN back again. Equivalently, the left and right cosets of NN coincide: gN=NggN = Ng for all gg.\n",
  "name": "Normal Subgroup",
